{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"GATE-DESIGN FINDING (from claiming tepid-bus-pomp, discovered with Joe): claiming a CHILD requires the PARENT epic to hold a fresh plan-review attestation (the claim of the child failed with 'Parent error: cannot claim <epic>: attestation is stale'). Two smells: (1) Converting the child to a BUG correctly exempts the bug's OWN plan-review — but the parent-epic coupling re-introduces the very friction the bug-exemption removes; should claiming a bug child require the parent epic's plan-review at all? (2) The epic's attestation is UNSCOPED (no file_impact + no citations → whole-HEAD freshness, the worm-folly-barge residual) so it goes stale on ANY commit, making the parent perpetually un-fresh during active multi-PR epic work. Candidates: exempt bug-children from the parent-review coupling; OR scope epic attestations (container file_impact = union of children?); OR don't require parent plan-review to claim a child (claim the parent's STATUS independently). Fold into the (a)-vs-(b) brainstorm."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782513379017006001,"uuid":"f762589f-cbdc-423c-a27a-8e7f95546a7c"}